<template>
  <svg id="svgCurve">
    <!-- <TestCurve1/> -->
    <TestCurve2/>
  </svg>
</template>

<script>
import axios from "axios";
import * as d3 from "d3";
import TestCurve1 from "@/components/TestCurve1.vue";
import TestCurve2 from "@/components/TestCurve2.vue";

export default {
  name: "TestCurve",
  data() {
    let pointStr = "[[0,0],[403,23],[35,35],[10,10]]";
    let data = JSON.parse(pointStr);

    return { data };
  },
  components: { TestCurve1,TestCurve2 },
  methods: {
    draw() {
      var points = [];
      // const target_copy = Object.assign({}, this.data);
      // for (var thing in target_copy)
      // {
      //   console.log(target_copy[thing][0]+","+target_copy[thing][1]);
      //   points.push(new Array(target_copy[thing][0],target_copy[thing][1]));
      // }
      // console.log(points);

      var points1 = TestCurve1.data();
      console.log(points1);
      for (var thing in points1.data) 
      {
        //points.push(points1.data[thing]);  ok
        var d1 = points1.data[thing][0]+5;
        var d2 = points1.data[thing][1]+5;
        points.push(new Array(d1,d2));
      }
      console.log(points);

      const curve = d3.line().curve(d3.curveNatural);

      d3.select("#divCurve").append("svg").attr("id", "svgCurve");

      d3.select("#svgCurve")
        .append("path")
        .attr("d", curve(points))
        .attr("stroke", "black")
        .attr("fill", "none");
    },
  },
  mounted() {
    this.draw();
  },
};
</script>
